Key Match Events: Donovan Mitchell scored a game-winning jumper with 3.1 seconds left to seal the Cavaliers' victory.
The Bucks held a 16-point lead but couldn't maintain it as the Cavaliers mounted a comeback.
Post-Match Reflections: Milwaukee coach Doc Rivers praised Andre Jackson Jr.'s defensive versatility and playmaking after giving him extended minutes over Pat Connaughton.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks' supporting cast struggled to score, with only 38 points from non-star players.
Gary Trent Jr. struggled offensively, shooting 1-of-10 with 3 points, 3 turnovers, and 3 fouls.
The Bucks improved their three-point shooting, hitting 46% (17/37) after a poor stretch in previous games.
